  <summary date="2020-08-04T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in Senate">City and State Diplomacy Act

This bill establishes within the Department of State the Office of Subnational Diplomacy, which shall supervise federal support for engagement by state, county,&#160;and municipal governments with foreign governments. The head of the office shall be the Ambassador-at-Large for Subnational Diplomacy, who shall be appointed by the President with the advice and consent of the Senate.</summary>
